# Card-audit puzzle (mtg-948 Part B) backing CLOSED issue mtg-540
# (Card Compatibility: Serendib Efreet).
#
# Aspects exercised:
#   1. T:Mode$ Phase | Phase$ Upkeep | ValidPlayer$ You | DealDamage 1 to You
#      — at the beginning of P0's upkeep, Serendib Efreet deals 1 damage to
#      its CONTROLLER (CR 603.2 beginning-of-upkeep trigger). This fires
#      automatically with no choice, so it is fully deterministic in the bulk
#      heuristic runner.
#   2. K:Flying — the 3/4 flier P1 cannot block, so it also connects in combat.
#
# P0 starts at turn=2 (its own upkeep is reached as the game advances), so the
# self-damage trigger fires and P0's life dips below 20. The flier then beats
# down P1 (at low life) for the win.
#
# HOW TO RUN / VERIFY interactively:
#   mtg tui --start-state test_puzzles/audit_serendib_efreet_upkeep_selfdamage.pzl \
#       --p1 heuristic --p2 heuristic --seed 42 -v 2 --no-color-logs
# The log shows "Trigger: Serendib Efreet ... deals 1 damage to you" on P0's
# upkeep (P0 life 20 -> 19), and the 3/4 flier attacking P1.

[metadata]
Name:Serendib Efreet upkeep self-damage + flying (audit mtg-540)
Goal:Win
Turns:5
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 controls a 3/4 flying Serendib Efreet. At the beginning of P0's upkeep the Efreet deals 1 damage to P0 (CR 603.2), so P0's life drops below 20. The flier P1 cannot block carries the game (P1 starts at 6 life). Assertions confirm the upkeep trigger fired, P0 took self-damage, and P0 still wins.

[state]
turn=2
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=
p0library=Island; Island; Island; Island; Island
p0graveyard=
p0battlefield=Serendib Efreet; Island; Island; Island
p0exile=

p1life=6
p1hand=
p1library=Forest; Forest; Forest; Forest; Forest
p1graveyard=
p1battlefield=Grizzly Bears; Forest
p1exile=

[assertions]
# The upkeep self-damage trigger fires: P0 takes at least 1 point of damage
# from its own Serendib Efreet (life < 20). This is the OBSERVABLE effect of
# the BeginningOfUpkeep DealDamage trigger. (We assert the life change, not a
# `trigger fired from Serendib Efreet` event, because the event log only emits
# LogEvent::TriggerFired for death/leaves-battlefield watcher triggers today,
# NOT for Phase/upkeep triggers — see the trigger-event instrumentation gap
# bug mtg-955.)
me life lt 20
# The 3/4 flier P1 cannot block carries the game.
game won
# P1 takes lethal flying damage.
opponent life le 0
